  "doc_id": "14841",
  "text": "Comparison of the mRNA profiles to the gene expression classifiers described for breast tumours [CITATION_1] consistently identified the normal breast samples as Class-Normal, MDAMB361 and HCC1419 as Luminal type A, and MCF7 as Luminal type B. BT20, PMC42, and HB4a clustered with the Basal and Her2 classifiers but their precise hierarchy varied depending on the algorithm employed (data not shown). PMC42 and HB4a also expressed many genes (notably, many collagen isoforms) attributed to the claudin-low mesenchymal/stromal/ fibroblast tumour subtype [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , but the importance of this classification in the context of cell lines awaits further investigation.",
